    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1952-03-11T15:58:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1952-03-11T15:58:00-05:00" n="142"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d142">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">762A.0221/3–1152: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 142<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Office of the United States High Commissioner for
                            Germany</gloss>, at Bonn</hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d142fn1">Drafted by <persName>Robert Klaber</persName> of
                            <gloss target="#t_GER1">GER</gloss> and cleared with <gloss
                            target="#t_GPA1">GPA</gloss>, <gloss target="#t_GAI1">GAI</gloss>, and
                            <gloss target="#t_GEA1">GEA</gloss>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1952-03-11T15:58:00-05:00"
                            >March 11, 1952—3:58 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1978. Subj: 1953 <gloss target="#t_GOAG1">GOAG</gloss> Budget. Below is verbatim
                    text Bur <gloss target="#t_GER1">Ger</gloss> Affrs draft statement basic policy
                    objectives for use 1953 budget highlight statement. Dept shld be consulted if
                        <gloss target="#t_HICOG1">HICOG</gloss> desires any changes fol draft.</p>
                <list>
                    <label>(1)</label>
                    <item>The maintenance of friendly and mutually beneficial relations between the
                        US and the <gloss target="#t_FedRep1">FedRep</gloss> of <gloss
                            target="#t_GER1">Ger</gloss>.</item>
                    <label>(2)</label>
                    <item>Continuing and effective participation by the <gloss target="#t_FedRep1"
                            >FedRep</gloss> on a basis of equality in the <gloss target="#t_EDC1"
                            >EDC</gloss>, itself within a developing Atlantic community, and in the
                        promotion of the polit, econ, and social welfare necessary to a strong and
                        durable Eur.</item>
                    <label>(3)</label>
                    <item>The maintenance of the allied position in Berlin and the <gloss
                            target="#t_Pol1">pol</gloss>, econ, and psychological strengthening of
                        the western sectors of Berlin.</item>
                    <label>(4)</label>
                    <item>Support of democratic elements in Germany and frustration of the Communist
                        aim to get control of all <gloss target="#t_GER1">Ger</gloss>.</item>
                    <label>(5)</label>
                    <item>
                        <p>The peaceful unification of all <gloss target="#t_GER1">Ger</gloss> under
                            conditions of freedom.</p>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="italic">End verbatim text</hi>.</p>
                    </item>
                </list>
                <p>Believe above statement will provide clear summary answer to question raised
                    recurrently by Cong and others of what is US fon <pb facs="0366" n="332"
                        xml:id="pg_332"/>
                    <gloss target="#t_Pol1">pol</gloss> toward <gloss target="#t_GER1">Ger</gloss>.
                    List pages 3 and 4 submission to <gloss target="#t_BudBur1">Bud Bur</gloss>
                    <note n="2" xml:id="d142fn2">Not further identified.</note> viewed as basic
                    functions or activities rather than policy aims and as such shld be retained in
                    Congressional submission to support requirements on level staffing, on staffing
                    not normal other missions and on level program expenses. However, redrafting nec
                    to avoid appearance repetition of above statement policy objectives and to
                    remove connotations offensive to <gloss target="#t_GER1">Ger</gloss>s,.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_AD1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
